Name: Check Google Store Visits
Notes:
Store Visits reports
The Store Visits reports contain the following key metrics:
    Store Visits: Number of visits to the store from users who initiated sessions on the website and then visited the store within 30 days. The number of visits for a given date is reported starting the day after, and may increase for the next 30 days as more users visit the store.
    Store Visit Rate: Number of store visits / number of sessions.
To access the reports:
    Sign in to Google Analytics.
    Navigate to your view.
    Open Reports.
    Select Conversions > Store Visits > Overview [or other desired report].

Name: Call Alex and Talk about Pixel Motion
Build Bakersfield Conquest Campaign
Notes:
APPROVED BY CLIENT

Let's Help Push Jeeps first in Google, then can expand to Chrysler/Fiat. Here is how we could do it.

We are going to do a target outbid on dealers selling SUVs in a 6 mile radius. When people search for something like Toyota Highlander our ad will say something along the lines of "Consider a Grand Cherokee - We're Only 5 Miles Away - Bakersfield Jeep" and then land them on the SRP for Grand Cherokee. This concept would pair big SUVs with Grand Cherokee, medium SUVs with Cherokee, and all-terrain vehicles such as Toyota 4runner with Wrangler Unlimited.

I always like to do a $500-$1000 "exploratory" budget to see how it performs and then adjust spend from there.

This would be a 10-mile radius.

Name: Check Maguire's Nissan & Maguire's Lincoln Data Studios
Chit Chat with DealerE Process about Adwords
Notes:
Troy was thinking we could take xt4 and xt5 while DealerE Process take the rest.

So looking into Cadillac a little more after our meeting, here is what I am seeing in the data…
 
Overall traffic to the website is down 38% from last month
Vehicle detail page views are up 6.7% over last month
Email leads are down 11% from last month (currently showing 32 email leads)
Carguru leads are down 73% from last month

 
Google AdWord (Dealer EProcess) has sent 662 clicks to the website with 42 conversions (phone call and form submits) averaging $2.19 per click.  I was able to log into their dashboard and they are bidding on New model terms, though XT4 isn’t in their keyword list yet.  It looks like the campaign with the other models is performing well – 89 clicks, average position when the ads show of 2.2, but I am guessing that with the limited budget of $2,500, we aren’t getting enough impression share to compete with the dealers that have a bigger budget.
 
I have attached a list of the calls that are a result of Adwords as well as the reporting for the current month. 
 
One thing I did notice is that the get a quote form requires both phone number and email.  If we can, we should make phone number optional. 
Also, the “call dealership” and “price watch” buttons are the only ones colored in on the SRP page, which makes them stand out.  I would suggest we make “price watch” white and have “request a quote” in color to make it stand out more.
